.TH "git-commit" "1" "" "Version Latest" "git-commit"
.hy
.SH git-commit
.SS DESCRIPTION
.PP
A commit utility function for \f[V]Git Add, Commit\f[R] and
\f[V]Push\f[R]
.SH EXAMPLE
.IP \[bu] 2
For one repository with an automatically generated message from the
files in the commit
.IP
.nf
\f[C]
git-commit
\f[R]
.fi
.IP \[bu] 2
For all repositories under the repo home directory with git exec
.IP
.nf
\f[C]
git exec git-commit \[dq]My Commit Message\[dq]
\f[R]
.fi
.SH SYNOPSIS
.IP
.nf
\f[C]
git-commit  [Commit Message]
\f[R]
.fi
.PP
If the commit message is not given, it will be generated with the files
in the commit.
.SS TIP
.PP
You can add it as alias in your \f[V]\[ti].gitconfig\f[R] Example with
\f[V]acp\f[R] that stands for \f[V]add, commit, push\f[R]
.IP
.nf
\f[C]
[alias]
  acp = \[dq]!git-commit\[dq]
\f[R]
.fi
